SIMPLE: zest
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zest
<hw>Zest</hw> <pr>(z⟦ecr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>zeste</ets>, probably fr. L. <ets>schistos</ets> split, cleft,
divided, Gr. <?/, from <?/ to split, cleave. Cf.
<er>Schism</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A piece of orange or lemon peel, or the aromatic oil
which may be squeezed from such peel, used to give flavor to liquor,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, something that gives or enhances a pleasant
taste, or the taste itself; an appetizer; also, keen enjoyment; relish;
gusto.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Almighty Vanity! to thee they owe⟦br⟧
Their <qex>zest</qex> of pleasure, and their balm of woe.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Liberality of disposition and conduct gives the highest
<qex>zest</qex> and relish to social intercourse.</q>
<rj><qau>Gogan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The woody, thick skin inclosing the kernel of a
walnut.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zest</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Zest
<hw>Zest</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Zested</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Zesting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cut into thin
slips, as the peel of an orange, lemon, etc.; to squeeze, as peel, over
the surface of anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give a relish or flavor to; to heighten the taste
or relish of; <as>as, to <ex>zest</ex> wine</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Gibber.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>zestful</ent>⟦br⟧
